{
  "video_id": "Y0xwmGM0DOY",
  "title": "Should we tax the rich more? | The Economist",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 3130.0,
      "end_time": 7410.0,
      "text": "Everyone depends on hospitals, roads, police and schools"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 7410.0,
      "end_time": 9380.0,
      "text": "but they're expensive"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 9380.0,
      "end_time": 11130.0,
      "text": "and governments across the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 11130.0,
      "end_time": 12293.0,
      "text": "are feeling the pinch."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 13160.0,
      "end_time": 15400.0,
      "text": "So, how can we continue in the future"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 15400.0,
      "end_time": 17740.0,
      "text": "to afford good quality public services?"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 17740.0,
      "end_time": 20173.0,
      "text": "Why has pressure on public services increased?"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 21610.0,
      "end_time": 23340.0,
      "text": "Populations are aging."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 23340.0,
      "end_time": 25610.0,
      "text": "As the number of retirees grows,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 25610.0,
      "end_time": 28200.0,
      "text": "working people are going to have to pay more taxes"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 28200.0,
      "end_time": 28852.0,
      "text": "to support them."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 30800.0,
      "end_time": 32860.0,
      "text": "And as healthcare technology improves,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 32860.0,
      "end_time": 35660.0,
      "text": "the cost of health care is also going to rise."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 35660.0,
      "end_time": 37349.0,
      "text": "But where to find the cash?"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 37350.0,
      "end_time": 40250.0,
      "text": "Basically governments can tax three things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 40250.0,
      "end_time": 42563.0,
      "text": "income, consumption or wealth."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 44630.0,
      "end_time": 46280.0,
      "text": "It's not your imagination."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 46280.0,
      "end_time": 48450.0,
      "text": "Income taxes really have been increasing"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 48450.0,
      "end_time": 50488.0,
      "text": "over the past 50 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 50488.0,
      "end_time": 53350.0,
      "text": "The evidence shows that taxes on income"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 53350.0,
      "end_time": 57157.0,
      "text": "including corporation tax discourage people from working."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 57157.0,
      "end_time": 59190.0,
      "text": "Countries with low income taxes"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 59200.0,
      "end_time": 63230.0,
      "text": "such as the UK tend to have stronger economic growth."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 63230.0,
      "end_time": 65289.0,
      "text": "Second, consumption."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 65290.00000000001,
      "end_time": 67820.0,
      "text": "This is things like sales tax in America"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 67820.0,
      "end_time": 70830.0,
      "text": "or value-added tax on purchases in Europe."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 70830.0,
      "end_time": 72580.0,
      "text": "One problem with consumption taxes"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 72580.0,
      "end_time": 74700.0,
      "text": "is that they hit poor people hardest"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 74700.0,
      "end_time": 77660.0,
      "text": "who spend more of their income on day-to-day expenses."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 77660.0,
      "end_time": 79479.0,
      "text": "Third, we have wealth taxes."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 79480.0,
      "end_time": 80560.0,
      "text": "This could be a better idea"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 80560.0,
      "end_time": 82290.0,
      "text": "than taxing income or consumption."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 82290.0,
      "end_time": 84220.0,
      "text": "This is partly because it places a higher levy"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 84220.0,
      "end_time": 85940.0,
      "text": "on the things that rich people have"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 85940.0,
      "end_time": 89000.0,
      "text": "such as property, and investments."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 89000.0,
      "end_time": 92620.0,
      "text": "Some economists advocate something called a land value tax"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 92620.0,
      "end_time": 94600.0,
      "text": "and this is basically where you tax"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 94600.0,
      "end_time": 95490.0,
      "text": "the value of plots of land"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 95490.0,
      "end_time": 97740.0,
      "text": "and this can raise a lot of money."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 97740.0,
      "end_time": 98740.0,
      "text": "A land value tax"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 98740.0,
      "end_time": 102230.0,
      "text": "has very few unintentional bad consequences."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 102930.0,
      "end_time": 104120.0,
      "text": "The problem is that taxing wealth"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 104120.0,
      "end_time": 106400.0,
      "text": "is not politically easy."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 106400.0,
      "end_time": 108170.0,
      "text": "Homeowners, for instance, are gonna be furious"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 108170.0,
      "end_time": 110300.0,
      "text": "if they're asked to pay higher property taxes"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 110300.0,
      "end_time": 113500.0,
      "text": "but if people want good government services,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 113500.0,
      "end_time": 114920.0,
      "text": "it's gonna need money."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 114920.0,
      "end_time": 117500.0,
      "text": "Taxes on wealth are always unpopular"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 117500.0,
      "end_time": 118789.0,
      "text": "but sooner or later, governments"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 118790.0,
      "end_time": 120740.0,
      "text": "are going to have to bite the bullet."
    }
  ]
}